<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Premeditate" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Premeditate,</orth> to revolve in the mind beforehand, to contrive or design previously: <cit><quote>he doth p. the dangers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 183" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 183</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--d welcomes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 94</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--d murder,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.170" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 170</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>deep --d lines,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 1</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>